# Python Style

- Prefer `ruff format` and `ruff check` as the default formatter/linter when available.
- Use type hints for public APIs; avoid `Any` unless justified.
- Avoid mutable default arguments (e.g., `def f(x=[])`).
- Avoid side effects at import time.
- Prefer `pathlib.Path` over string paths.
- Use `logging` (not `print`) for non-CLI code.
